  <part id="gegl">
    <title>GEGL Overview</title>
      <partintro>
        <para>
        GEGL (GEneric Graphical Library) is an image processing
        library based on GObjects. This library is designed to handle
        various image processing tasks needed in Gimp initially, but
        should be useful to other apps as well. It handles color
        spaces and data types in a general way, and allows adding new
        color models/data types easily. It includes a way of creating
        chains (or trees) of image operations and evaluating these in
        a demand-driven way. Classes for point, area, geometric and
        statistics operations are included, as well as color
        conversion ops for converting images between color models. It
        has memory management and image classes as well.
        </para>
        <para>
        GEGL is still in early development and is not ready for use as
        a library.  This documentation is intended for GEGL developers
        and is not intended to be complete.
        </para>
        <para>
        </para>

        <para>
        GEGL consists of the following:
          <variablelist>

            <varlistentry>
              <term>GEGL Library</term>
              <listitem>
	      <para>
		The GEGL library itself contains
		image <firstterm>operators</firstterm>, such
		as <link linkend="GeglOver">GeglOver</link> and
		<link linkend="GeglAdd">GeglAdd</link>, which describe
		image operations with inputs and outputs.
              </para>
	      </listitem>
            </varlistentry>

            <varlistentry>
            <term>Unit Tests</term>
            <listitem>
	      <para>
		The unit tests for the GEGL library used for
		development and testing.
            </para></listitem>
            </varlistentry>

          </variablelist>
        </para>
      </partintro>
  </part>

